  "response": "There is no credible evidence or historical consensus supporting the claim that Jawaharlal Nehru, the first Prime Minister of India, was a Muslim. Nehru was born into a Hindu Brahmin family on November 14, 1889, and he identified as a Hindu throughout his life. His family, the Nehrus, has been a well-documented Hindu lineage.\n\nClaims questioning Nehru's religious identity often stem from various political, social, or ideological motivations rather than historical facts. Such assertions lack substantial evidence and are typically regarded as misinformation or conspiracy theories.\n\nIn historical discussions, it's essential to rely on verified information and credible sources. If you have further questions or seek more information about Nehru's life and contributions, feel free to ask!",
